title: Mortality of tobacco budworms
description:
Description
For three days, moths of the tobacco budworm (Heliothis virescens) were exposed 
to doses of the pyrethroid trans-cypermethrin.
reference:
In Venables and Ripley (2002), these data are analysed using a logistic regression with base-2 logarithm of dose 
as explanatory variable.

parameters.numdead: a numeric vector of dead or knocked-down moths
parameters.dose: a numeric vector of dose values (\mu g)
parameters.total: a numeric vector of total number of moths
parameters.sex: a factor with levels F M denoting a grouping according to sex

format: A data frame with 12 observations on the following 4 variables.
